title: Ó Maoilmhichil
text:
Ó Maoilmhichil is an uncommon surname of <a href="Irish%20language">Irish</a> origin devolving into the common Irish surnames <a href="Mitchell%20%28surname%29">Mitchell</a> and <a href="Mulvihill">Mulvihill</a>.
The surname <a href="Mitchell%20%28surname%29">Mitchell</a> is derived from the <a href="Sept">Sept</a> or <a href="Clan">Clan</a> name Uí Mhaoilmhichil which means Patrons or Devotees of <a href="Michael%20%28archangel%29">Saint Michael the Archangel</a>.
As the English language began to replace <a href="Irish%20language">Irish</a> and <a href="Scottish%20Gaelic">Scottish Gaelic</a>, the surname was <a href="anglicisation">anglicized</a> as <a href="Mitchell%20%28surname%29">Mitchell</a>, <a href="Michael">Michael</a>, <a href="Mulvihill">Mulvihill</a>, <a href="Mulville">Mulville</a>, or <a href="Melville%20%28surname%29">Melville</a>, and other variations. 
A family motto "<a href="Pro%20aris%20et%20focis">Pro aris et focis</a>" originates from the Irish family name "Mulvihill".
